The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Sunday, June 06, 2004 				Metro Recommends
 THE BOOK 

	(Christopher Pinney) The political struggle in India portrayed through printed images is the subject of the book, lavishly illustrated with pictures. Through unfamiliar images, the author takes the reader on a journey of discovery of the nationalist movement, from an unusual angle. THE SHOW 				 																																	(The History Channel, June 6, 9 pm) The programme explores the legend of Troy, as told by its blind story-teller Homer. A figment of the authors imagination or true story, the epic battle and tale of one city has captured imaginations through the centuries. THE FILM				 																																	(INOX) Harry , Ron and Hermione are teenagers now. The mystery deepens and new characters enter the story in J.K. Rowlings third tale in the series. The saga continues in the wizard world, as the three friends battle the dark forces to keep Voldemort at bay. 

